  "prompt": "Which are the best institutes in Germany for masters in automotive engineering?",
  "response": "Germany is known for its strong automotive industry and offers several excellent institutes for master's programs in automotive engineering. Here are some of the top institutions you might consider:\n\n1. **Technische Universit\u00e4t M\u00fcnchen (TUM)** - TUM offers a Master's in Mobility Science, which encompasses automotive engineering topics and collaborates closely with industry leaders.\n\n2. **RWTH Aachen University** - RWTH Aachen is renowned for its engineering programs, and its Mechanical Engineering program includes comprehensive automotive engineering coursework.\n\n3. **Karlsruhe Institute of Technology (KIT)** - KIT is another leading technical university with a strong focus on engineering, including specializations in automotive technology.\n\n4. **Technische Universit\u00e4t Stuttgart** - This university has strong programs in mechanical engineering, with specific courses and research focused on automotive engineering.\n\n5. **Friedrich-Alexander-Universit\u00e4t Erlangen-N\u00fcrnberg (FAU)** - The university offers a master's program in automotive engineering, focusing on vehicle technology and production systems.\n\n6. **Daimler AG and University of Stuttgart Collaboration** - Through partnerships with major automotive companies, programs focus on practical applications in automotive engineering.\n\n7. **Hochschule f\u00fcr Technik Stuttgart (HFT Stuttgart)** - HFT Stuttgart offers specialized master's programs in automotive engineering with a focus on current industry practices.\n\n8. **HTW Berlin (Hochschule f\u00fcr Technik und Wirtschaft)** - Offers a Master's program related to automotive systems engineering, focusing on modern automotive technologies.\n\nWhen considering a program, it\u2019s essential to look at the specific curriculum, faculty expertise, industry connections, and research opportunities available at each institution. Additionally, language requirements (many programs are offered in English, but some may require knowledge of German) and the location related to the automotive industry may also influence your decision.",
